Scope and Contents

This series contains gay male-themed erotic pulp novels written around the 1970s to the 1990s.

Extent

Scope and Contents

This series contains zines, which include erotic stories, pictures, writings, and reader-submitted content. Some zines were produced by lesser-known gay porn producers and production companies, while others evolved into formal magazine publications during their print run.

Arrangement

Series XII. Work Files, 1964-2008, undated

langmaterial

English

Extent

1 linear foot in one record carton.
1 electronic discs (cd-rom)

Scope and Contents

Most of these files are related to the book Marshall was working on before his death: "Masters of Homoerotic Drawings." Files include a draft/mock-up of the book, containing images and title pages. This series also contains what was most likely research, including erotic magazines; exhibition catalogues, announcements, and invitations; images with a sexual theme; a CD-R disc of images, and correspondence.

Arrangement

This series has not been arranged by an archivist. Material was placed in acid free folders when necessary. The materials are arranged in the order in which they were received from the donor.
